missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:1:# Attack on Chain 02 - Spectator-Leakage Lower-Bound Ledger
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:9:- It attacks the live mission mismatch directly: exact NS may realize some desired channels yet still fail to isolate them.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:10:- It has an honest failure mode. An explicit vanishing-leakage family would be real anti-obstruction evidence, not wasted effort.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:15:### Step 1 - Freeze one leakage functional and one closure rule
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:19:- The chain acts as if one can simply "choose" a leakage functional, but the whole mission already knows that this choice is dangerous. Ratios like off-graph interaction strength divided by on-graph interaction strength are not automatically invariant under packetization, normalization, basis choice, or time-window choice.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:21:- The proposed closure conventions are not clean alternatives on the same footing. Exact Fourier support closure, helical triad closure, and conjugate completion are different layers of bookkeeping, not one menu of mutually exclusive rules.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:26:- The kill condition is too late and too weak. If no invariant leakage functional exists, this chain should not "redirect" after trying Step 1; it should admit that it was downstream of an unresolved prerequisite from the start.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:32:- "Smallest candidate packets" is a hidden thesis. A leakage lower bound proved only for minimal packets may say nothing about larger packets with redundancy, compensating geometry, or distributed role assignment.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:33:- The ledger language encourages overcounting. A mode can be kinematically forced yet dynamically negligible, cancelled, or damped on the time scale that matters for Tao-like behavior.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:34:- The proposed spectator classes are not obviously disjoint in a way that supports clean lower bounds. Mirror modes, companion triads, and feedback channels can interact with each other, so classwise accounting may double-count or hide cancellations.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:39:- "Finite-packet non-closure" is not automatically a stronger obstruction. It only kills one model class. The mission target is near-closed Tao-like behavior, not necessarily strict finite packet closure.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:45:- A closure ledger is only kinematic data. A lower bound requires showing that the forced channels contribute in a norm and on a time scale that actually competes with the desired Tao-like channels.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:46:- "Same normalization" is not a trivial bookkeeping step. Interaction coefficients, energy flux, and amplitude production are different objects. A bound in one may be irrelevant in another.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:47:- The plan assumes exact coefficient identities and projection geometry can produce sign-definite inequalities. In helical triad algebra, many terms are sign-indefinite and phase-sensitive. The generic outcome is cancellation structure, not monotone leakage.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:52:- The kill condition only asks whether every spectator term can cancel simultaneously. That is too binary. The more realistic failure mode is softer: no uniform positive lower bound survives, but no explicit arbitrarily-small-leakage family is yet found either.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:71:- The chain presents a false dichotomy: either positive infimum leakage or an explicit vanishing-leakage family. There is a large middle ground where leakage decays along families but not cleanly enough to be theorem-ready.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:73:- An explicit low-leakage family is not yet a serious anti-obstruction result unless it also preserves the Tao-like role logic over a meaningful time window. Instantaneous low leakage is weaker than near-circuit dynamics.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:82:- Dependency inversion: this chain really depends on Chain 04. Without a stable object definition, "leakage" can be tuned by bookkeeping and the whole program becomes selection-biased.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:86:- Redundancy risk: unless it delivers a genuinely invariant lower bound or a sharp low-leakage family, it overlaps heavily with the mission's already-known "unavoidable spectator couplings" story and adds little beyond nicer packaging.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:92:- an invariant leakage functional plus a real positive lower bound on an explicit packet class, or
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:93:- an explicit family showing leakage can be driven arbitrarily low, which would materially weaken the firewall story.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/final-decider.md:1:# Final Decision Memo - exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit / run-001
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/final-decider.md:6:`/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/winning-chain.md`
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/final-decider.md:9:**Co-Evolving Definition Freeze and Exact Interaction Audit With Invariant Downstream Gates**
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/final-decider.md:16:  It already has the strongest audited floor: even if no usable near-closed Tao-circuit notion survives, it can return a bounded negative that names the failure type precisely: imprecision, non-robustness after canonicalization, or lack of theorem utility after exact interaction analysis. That is a cleaner presentable product than the likely failure modes of the other branches.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/final-decider.md:20:  Chain 02 explicitly depends on a frozen object. Chain 03 also needs an invariant admissibility sheet before its search claims are trustworthy. Chain 01 is therefore the branch that unlocks the others while still being independently presentable.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/final-decider.md:34:- From **Chain 03**: exact packet testing must use hard admissibility filters and a diagnostic vector rather than a soft aggregate score, so later handoff to adversarial search remains representation-stable and non-cosmetic.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/final-decider.md:40:- one or two exact, testable near-circuit notions with explicit downstream gates; or
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The weakness is that it tries to turn a hard object-definition and theorem-calibration problem into a search-and-score problem too early. In this mission, that is dangerous. If "near-closed Tao circuit" has not already survived the Chain 04 invariance audit, then Step 1 just invents a proxy and the rest of the chain optimizes that proxy. Then Step 5 overclaims in both directions: a small-packet partial mimic is treated as a clean kill of the firewall idea, while small-family failure is treated as informative obstruction. Neither inference is earned by the current design.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:17:- The score mixes fundamentally different requirements: sign pattern, channel separation, rotor dominance, spectator leakage, and delayed-threshold behavior. Those are not obviously commensurable. A scalar score can hide the fact that one catastrophic failure is being compensated by two cosmetic wins.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:23:Failure mode: Step 1 produces a tidy scorecard that later stages start treating as the mission object, even though it is only one ad hoc surrogate for that object.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- The chain says "full conjugate completion," which is necessary but not sufficient. The real burden is exact closure under all forced interactions, not just mirror completion. Once that is imposed honestly, the "small family" may stop being small.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:31:- The search family menu is not evidently exhaustive in the right sense. A shell-bridging packet, two linked triads, and similar templates may miss the one geometric arrangement where unwanted channels partially cancel.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:39:This step front-loads algebraic screening in a way that can easily confuse static coefficient structure with dynamical viability.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:41:- Exact interaction tables are necessary. Using them as the main pre-simulation ranking device is much shakier. Delayed transfer depends on amplitudes, phase evolution, and timescale interplay, not just raw coefficient tables.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:42:- "Discard candidates that fail immediately on signs, forced feedback, or overwhelming spectators" sounds crisp but is actually ambiguous. Overwhelming relative to what: coefficient size, initial amplitude, one activation window, or net energy flux?
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:43:- Large spectator coefficients are not automatically fatal if the relevant spectator modes stay weak on the relevant timescale. Small feedback coefficients are not automatically harmless if they act on the wrong variable with the wrong sign for long enough.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:44:- This step overlaps heavily with Chain 02. Once the chain builds an exact coupling ledger, classifies spectators, and ranks by leakage-like criteria, it is already doing a weakened version of the lower-bound chain before it reaches any construction-specific dynamics.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:54:- The phrase "reduced exact amplitude systems" is the crux. If the candidate is only near-closed, what exactly is being integrated? A truly exact closed packet, or a reduced subsystem obtained by dropping forced modes? If it is the latter, the dynamic test is already compromised.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:57:- Delayed-threshold behavior is stiff and phase-sensitive. One or two hand-picked trajectories are not strong evidence. A candidate could "work" only under fine-tuned initial phases or fail once viscosity, shell spacing, or amplitude normalization are varied honestly.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:78:Chain 03 is supposed to coexist with Chain 04, but in practice it tries to bypass it. If the stable definition of "near-closed Tao circuit" is not already fixed, then "Tao-likeness" becomes whatever this chain's score function says it is. That makes the search output hard to trust and hard to compare with the other chains.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:82:The mission asks about an exact no-near-closed-Tao-circuit statement. A tiny packet that partially mimics pump / seed / amplifier / rotor logic does not by itself refute the broader obstruction. It may only show that one naive formulation was too strict.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:90:Steps 1 through 3 already revolve around leakage, forced spectators, and exact interaction ledgers. The difference only appears once Step 4 starts dynamic testing. So much of the chain duplicates the lower-bound route but with a looser metric and stronger dependence on search heuristics.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:111:That is not obviously the "fastest" route inside a 3-5 exploration mission budget, especially when Chain 04 is supposed to gate the object definition first.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:118:- Even failure could be useful if the output is written modestly as a diagnostic about small exact packets, not as a global theorem surrogate.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:124:The right way to view it is: if Chain 04 first freezes a stable, representation-invariant notion of near-closure, then Chain 03 can become a valuable stress test against that object. Without that gate, it mostly searches for a high score on its own surrogate. And even in the best case, a small exact survivor should be treated as serious anti-obstruction evidence, not an automatic clean kill of the firewall idea.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md:50:This lands cleanly. The original edge-case list is heavily inherited from the prior non-isolability narrative, so it is not a neutral stress test. The attacker is right that the audit must include cases favorable to the opposite conclusion as well: engineered helical sign patterns, sparse triad geometries, scale-separated families, and cases where leakage exists but is dynamically negligible.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md:58:The attacker is right that one surviving definition does not automatically mean one canonical mission object. Different downstream routes may need different notions, especially if one is leakage-based and another is behavior-based. The original chain also moves too quickly from "no candidate survived my audit" to "the mission fails at definition level," even though earlier audits may have been too strict.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md:81:6. Permit one repair or splitting round so that a leakage-based notion and a behavioral notion can separate if the math demands it.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md:91:- a split outcome in which one leakage-style notion and one behavior-style notion survive as distinct downstream targets.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-04.md:1:# Chain 04 - Definition-Stability Audit for "Near-Closed Tao Circuit"
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-04.md:5:The prior mission already identified that "exact-NS circuit non-isolability" failed because it was not yet a concrete object. The cleanest early kill is to test whether any precise definition of a near-closed Tao circuit remains stable under the unavoidable exact symmetries and bookkeeping choices of Fourier/helical NS.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-04.md:11:- one stable definition family of "near-closed Tao circuit" that later chains can use without hidden normalization tricks; or
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-04.md:26:leakage-ratio closure,
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-04.md:27:or delayed-threshold behavioral closure.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-04.md:39:Action: test each definition against exact symmetries and bookkeeping changes that should not change the mathematical content: rescaling, phase rotation, helical basis choice, conjugate completion, and packet regrouping.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-04.md:53:Action: require each candidate to yield a finite interaction table, a finite leakage metric, or a finite-time behavioral test.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:1:# Selector - exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit / run-001
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:5:1. Chain 04 - Definition-Stability Audit for "Near-Closed Tao Circuit"
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:6:2. Chain 02 - Spectator-Leakage Lower-Bound Ledger
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:9:These three make the strongest portfolio because they cover the full mission risk surface without collapsing into one obstruction style. Chain 04 is the prerequisite gatekeeper: if the object is unstable or circular, later theorem work is fake. Chain 02 then attacks the inherited exact-NS non-isolability pressure in its most mission-aligned quantitative form, and it still pays off on failure because a vanishing-leakage family would become explicit anti-obstruction evidence. Chain 03 preserves the highest-upside adversarial route by directly trying to beat the obstruction with an exact small packet, so the portfolio does not overfit to one no-circuit narrative.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:13:### 1. Chain 04 - Definition-Stability Audit for "Near-Closed Tao Circuit"
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:17:### 2. Chain 02 - Spectator-Leakage Lower-Bound Ledger
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:19:Best positive-obstruction route after Chain 04 because it directly targets the inherited pressure that exact NS cannot isolate Tao's five-role circuit. It is broader and more mission-central than a pure coefficient-rigidity claim, and if the lower bound fails it still produces an explicit low-leakage family that usefully feeds the adversarial construction path.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:25:### 4. Chain 01 - Minimal Helical Coefficient-Rigidity Theorem
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:27:Strong and clean, but ranked fourth because it is the narrowest obstruction route and the most brittle to geometric escape hatches. If the ratio-rigidity thesis breaks, its likely value is mostly diagnostic redirection into the leakage and construction routes already covered by Chains 02 and 03, so it adds less portfolio diversity than those alternatives.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The original chain points at a real mission-aligned pressure point: exact Navier-Stokes may realize some desired Tao-role channels while still failing to isolate them. But the chain treated "leakage" as if it could be chosen by bookkeeping, delayed the geometry and helicity adversary too long, and moved too quickly from forced couplings to a dynamical obstruction claim.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:7:The right repair is not to discard the chain. It is to narrow it into a downstream quantitative test that only starts after a stable near-closure object is fixed, uses one invariant dynamical observable, treats minimal packets as calibration rather than theorem scope, and allows an honest middle outcome where the leakage route itself fails to produce a class-uniform theorem.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:15:This is the load-bearing criticism. The original Step 1 acted as if one could simply choose a leakage functional and closure rule, but this mission already identified object-definition instability as a first-order risk. Also, exact Fourier support closure, helical triad bookkeeping, and conjugate completion are not interchangeable options on one level. The refined chain should therefore begin only after one stable near-closure object has been frozen, ideally by Chain 04.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:21:The attacker is right that a theorem proved only for minimal packets may miss redundancy, distributed role assignment, or small tails. The attacker is also right that a forced ledger can overstate importance if it counts channels that are dynamically negligible or cancellation-prone. But starting with minimal packets is still a reasonable calibration move. The defect was not using them first; it was letting them implicitly define the whole theorem class.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:39:The original finish allowed only two clean endings: positive leakage bound or explicit vanishing-leakage family. That misses the likely middle case where the route fails because the observable is not invariant enough, the cancellations destroy coercivity, or the bound depends too strongly on packet-class choices. The refined chain should permit that meta-obstruction as a presentable output.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:41:### 6. The whole chain risks redundancy unless it earns an invariant lower bound, an explicit low-leakage family, or a precise obstruction to the leakage route itself
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:45:This warning is fair, but it is not a refutation. The chain does overlap with the already-known "forced spectators exist" story if it stops at a prettier ledger. Still, a sharp failure diagnosis can be valuable here. If the refined chain can say exactly why no class-uniform leakage theorem emerges, that is more than redundant packaging.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:52:2. It chooses one invariant dynamical leakage observable before any ledger is built.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:54:4. It allows three honest endings: a restricted-class positive lower bound, an explicit low-leakage family that preserves Tao-role logic over a stated window, or a precise obstruction showing why leakage-based arguments do not yield a presentable theorem.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:64:- The most plausible success mode is not a universal no-near-closure theorem, but either a restricted-class leakage bound or a clean diagnosis of why the leakage program cannot support such a theorem without stronger hypotheses.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:1:# Chain 01 - Minimal Helical Coefficient-Rigidity Theorem
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:5:A Tao-like circuit needs a deliberately ordered hierarchy of effective channels:
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:9:In exact Navier-Stokes, those channels arise from one helical/Fourier interaction law whose coefficients are rigid functions of triad geometry, helicity signs, and Leray projection. The route is to show that a minimal exact packet cannot realize the required hierarchy with the needed sign pattern.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:16:- a sharp failure memo showing that coefficient rigidity alone is too weak and that leakage, not ratio incompatibility, is the real obstruction.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:20:This chain is about coefficient hierarchy inside the desired channels themselves. It does not primarily rely on spectator-mode proliferation, numerical search, or definition-only critique.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:24:### Step 1 - Freeze one exact notion of a Tao-like channel hierarchy
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:28:Action: define one concrete near-circuit object in the minimal language needed for this chain: a finite helical packet, five labeled effective roles, admissible sign pattern, and one explicit dominance vector comparing desired channel sizes to each other.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:30:Action: keep the definition narrow enough that it can fail honestly. Do not bundle spectator leakage into the object beyond a small bookkeeping parameter.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:40:Action: enumerate the smallest plausible support families, likely one or two linked helical triads plus the conjugate completion forced by reality.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:42:Action: reject larger families unless a smaller family is proven incapable even before coefficient analysis.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:46:Kill condition: if the minimal support already explodes into an uncontrolled large packet before any coefficient work, record that as evidence for Chain 02 and stop this chain.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:48:### Step 3 - Derive the exact projected amplitude equations and coefficient identities
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:52:Action: write the exact helical amplitude system for the chosen support, including all cyclic coefficients and any identities forced by energy/helicity conservation and Leray projection.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:56:Expected output: an interaction table with exact coefficients, sign constraints, and the derived ratio relations among the targeted channels.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:68:Expected output: either a proposition draft with assumptions and conclusion, or an explicit parameter family that escapes the naive rigidity claim.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:76:Action: if rigidity wins, state the cleanest theorem object possible, naming the minimal packet, the exact forbidden hierarchy, and the first missing lemma.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:78:Action: if rigidity loses, write a bounded negative result explaining exactly which ratio freedom survives and why coefficient rigidity alone is not the right firewall object.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md:80:Expected output: a proposition candidate or a narrow negative memo that redirects later work toward leakage or construction.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-03.md:11:- a concrete exact helical/Fourier packet with explicit coefficients and dynamics that honestly approximates Tao's pump / seed / amplifier / rotor / transfer logic; or
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-03.md:24:Action: choose a small set of quantitative criteria for approximate success: desired sign pattern, separation between seed and amplifier channels, rotor dominance, small spectator leakage, and one delayed-threshold proxy.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-03.md:36:Action: generate a bounded search family, such as one linked-triad packet, two linked-triad packets, and one shell-bridging packet, each with full conjugate completion.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-03.md:60:Action: integrate the reduced exact amplitude systems for the best one or two candidates and check whether they actually exhibit delayed growth, threshold behavior, and transfer without immediate spectator takeover.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-03.md:62:Action: compare observed behavior against the scorecard rather than improvising qualitative claims.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selected/chain-01.md:1:# Chain 04 - Definition-Stability Audit for "Near-Closed Tao Circuit"
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selected/chain-01.md:5:The prior mission already identified that "exact-NS circuit non-isolability" failed because it was not yet a concrete object. The cleanest early kill is to test whether any precise definition of a near-closed Tao circuit remains stable under the unavoidable exact symmetries and bookkeeping choices of Fourier/helical NS.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selected/chain-01.md:11:- one stable definition family of "near-closed Tao circuit" that later chains can use without hidden normalization tricks; or
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selected/chain-01.md:26:leakage-ratio closure,
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selected/chain-01.md:27:or delayed-threshold behavioral closure.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selected/chain-01.md:39:Action: test each definition against exact symmetries and bookkeeping changes that should not change the mathematical content: rescaling, phase rotation, helical basis choice, conjugate completion, and packet regrouping.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selected/chain-01.md:53:Action: require each candidate to yield a finite interaction table, a finite leakage metric, or a finite-time behavioral test.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:1:# Planner Portfolio - exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit / run-001
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:6:- The inherited live discrepancy is not generic pressure rhetoric. It is exact-NS circuit non-isolability: exact Navier-Stokes supplies one rigid Leray-projected quadratic law plus full triad summation, while Tao's circuit needs a near-isolated hierarchy of five channels.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:7:- Prior work already isolated the three load-bearing exact-NS pressures on the idea: coefficient rigidity, unavoidable spectator couplings, and exact projection/reality bookkeeping.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:8:- Prior work did not yet produce a theorem object, leakage lower bound, or counterexample. This run must do that rather than restating "NS is more entangled."
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:13:### Chain 01 - Minimal Helical Coefficient-Rigidity Theorem
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:15:Central premise: the smallest exact helical packet capable of mimicking Tao's pump / seed / amplifier / rotor logic already fails because the required sign and magnitude hierarchy cannot be realized by one geometry-locked family of triad coefficients.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:17:### Chain 02 - Spectator-Leakage Lower-Bound Ledger
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:19:Central premise: even if some desired channels can be matched, exact Fourier/helical closure plus mirror-mode bookkeeping forces enough extra interactions that any honest Tao-like subsystem leaks a quantifiable amount of activity outside the five target roles.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:25:### Chain 04 - Definition-Stability Audit for "Near-Closed Tao Circuit"
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:27:Central premise: the whole mission may fail at the object-definition level. If every reasonable definition of near-closure is unstable under phase choice, packetization, scaling, or conjugate completion, the right result is a sharp definitional kill rather than a fake theorem program.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:31:- Chain 01 is algebraic and theorem-facing. It targets incompatible coefficient ratios and sign patterns inside a minimal exact helical model.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:32:- Chain 02 is closure- and leakage-facing. It assumes desired channels may exist but asks whether forced spectators can be bounded below.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:38:- Every chain must freeze one exact target object before optimism begins: either a minimal helical packet, a leakage functional, a concrete search family, or a formal definition family.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:46:- Second priority: Chain 01, because coefficient rigidity is the cleanest exact mechanism-level theorem target.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:47:- Third priority: Chain 02, because leakage is the most natural quantitative fallback if pure rigidity does not close.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:1:# Chain 02 - Spectator-Leakage Lower-Bound Ledger
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:5:The strongest surviving mismatch may not be that desired Tao channels are impossible, but that exact NS cannot keep them isolated. Once one activates the needed triads, exact closure under `p + q = k`, Leray projection, and mirror-mode completion forces extra channels. The route is to turn that into a quantitative leakage lower bound.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:11:- a lower bound showing that any exact packet realizing the desired Tao-like channels must leak at least a fixed fraction of interaction strength or energy flux into spectator modes; or
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:12:- a precise negative result showing that leakage can in fact be made arbitrarily small in some explicit family.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:16:This chain accepts that some desired couplings may exist and focuses instead on unavoidable extra couplings. It is graph-closure and leakage-based, not coefficient-ratio based or adversarially constructive.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:20:### Step 1 - Freeze one leakage functional and one closure rule
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:24:Action: define a finite target circuit graph and one quantitative leakage measure, for example the ratio of forced off-graph interaction strength to on-graph interaction strength, or the minimum spectator amplitude production over one activation window.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:26:Action: choose one closure convention in advance: exact Fourier support closure, helical triad closure, and conjugate completion under `u^(-k) = conjugate(u^k)`.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:28:Expected output: a leakage-definition sheet with one formula for "near-closed" and one exact closure rule.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:30:Kill condition: if no leakage functional is invariant enough to compare different packet realizations honestly, stop and redirect to Chain 04.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:36:Action: start from a minimal packet that realizes the intended Tao roles and compute the full list of same-scale, conjugate, and cross-scale interactions forced by the closure rule.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:40:Expected output: a closure ledger listing desired channels, forced spectator channels, and the structural reason each spectator appears.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:48:Action: express each spectator class in the same normalization as the desired channels so the comparison is honest.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:50:Action: derive candidate lower bounds from exact coefficient identities, reality symmetry, and projection geometry rather than heuristic "many couplings" language.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:54:Kill condition: if every spectator term can simultaneously cancel by phase choice or geometry without violating the desired channels, the lower-bound premise is broken and the chain should hand off to Chain 03.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:60:Action: search the allowed geometry families for worst-case leakage, including near-degenerate or specially aligned helical configurations.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:62:Action: identify whether the infimum leakage is positive, merely bounded in a weaker norm, or tends to zero along an explicit family.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:64:Expected output: a stress-test memo with the best surviving lower bound or an explicit vanishing-leakage family.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:72:Action: if the infimum leakage stays positive, formulate the cleanest no-near-closure statement available, naming the packet class, leakage functional, and bound.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:74:Action: if the infimum leakage tends to zero, record the exact family that beats the leakage route and pass it to the adversarial construction chain.
