missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:1:# Refined Chain 03 - Invariant-Gated Adversarial Exact Packet Search
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:5:The constructive search route is worth keeping, but only if it stops optimizing an ad hoc "Tao-likeness" surrogate and instead searches within a fixed exact admissibility framework. The goal is to find the smallest honest exact packet class that survives exact closure and still shows meaningful Tao-like delayed transfer behavior, or else to produce a bounded diagnostic atlas of why such small packets fail.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:12:- a bounded failure atlas for normalized small exact packet classes, listing the exact mechanisms that block Tao-like behavior under honest closure.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:20:### Step 1 - Freeze an invariant admissibility sheet before searching
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:24:Action: fix one exact closure rule, one normalization convention for equivalence classes, and one representation-invariant admissibility sheet for this search. The admissibility sheet should be a vector of hard conditions, not a single scalar score.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:26:Action: include only features that can be stated honestly before dynamics, such as exact channel presence, forbidden feedback absence, spectator-class bounds in a fixed normalization, and symmetry conventions. Do not include a delayed-threshold proxy here.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:28:Expected output: an admissibility memo defining exact closure, normalization, pass/fail filters, and comparison conventions.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:30:Kill condition: if no invariant-enough admissibility sheet can be stated for the searched class, stop and hand off rather than optimizing an ad hoc surrogate.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:38:Action: for each family, expand the full forced closure honestly, not just conjugate completion, and record the resulting exact packet size.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:48:Action: compute exact interaction tables for all candidates and apply only hard admissibility filters at this stage: exact closure, required channel presence, forbidden feedback exclusion, and spectator bounds in one fixed norm or activation window.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:50:Action: retain a non-aggregated diagnostic vector for each survivor so later interpretation can see which constraints are barely passed and which are robustly passed. Do not collapse this into one scalar ranking.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:62:Action: integrate only the honest exact closed systems, including all forced modes. Test whether the candidates show delayed transfer, threshold behavior, and spectator subordination over a stated window.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:16:### 1. Step 1 surrogate-score problem
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:27:Refinement: replace the scalar score with hard admissibility filters plus a small diagnostic vector. Remove any pre-dynamics delayed-threshold term.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:33:The critique is right that tiny packets may miss the first genuine survivor and that conjugate completion alone is not enough; exact forced closure must be accounted for. But bounded small-family search is still a legitimate adversarial tactic, provided the claims are scoped correctly.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:55:- define any leakage or spectator threshold in one fixed normalization;
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:88:The critique is right that the chain becomes unreliable if "near-closed Tao circuit" is allowed to float with the score function. But the search does not need a full theorem-ready object before it can do useful work. It does need one invariant local admissibility sheet for the search class.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:92:- add an opening gate that fixes exact closure, normalization, and comparison conventions;
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:93:- if that gate fails, the chain stops and hands off rather than optimizing an ad hoc surrogate.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:99:There is real overlap in closure bookkeeping, leakage accounting, and spectator classification. Still, the chains are not redundant.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:101:- Chain 02 asks for a lower bound or vanishing-leakage family.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:122:- it must begin with an invariant admissibility gate;
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-03.md:125:- it must present itself as a bounded adversarial stress test, not a mission-deciding theorem surrogate.
