missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:94:The score, family menu, ranking scheme, and simulation shortlist are all heuristic choices. That is acceptable for adversarial exploration. It is not acceptable if the final memo is going to speak in theorem-adjacent language about what exact NS can or cannot do.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:19:Best positive-obstruction route after Chain 04 because it directly targets the inherited pressure that exact NS cannot isolate Tao's five-role circuit. It is broader and more mission-central than a pure coefficient-rigidity claim, and if the lower bound fails it still produces an explicit low-leakage family that usefully feeds the adversarial construction path.
missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:23:Central premise: the obstruction might be false. The fastest honest kill is to search directly for the best exact NS or helical packet that approximates Tao's logic and see whether it survives exact coupling accounting.
