+# Exploration 002 Report - Exact Interaction Templates And Downstream Gates
+
+## Goal
+
+Attach one exact Fourier / helical interaction template and one honest
+downstream gate to each promoted Step-2 candidate, then decide whether Chain
+Step 3 is now well-posed.
+
+## Sources Used
+
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-002/GOAL.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-001/RESULTS.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-001/GOAL.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/final-decider.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md`
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md`
+- `library/meta/obstruction-screening/demand-estimate-level-action-on-the-live-obstruction.md`
+- `library/meta/obstruction-screening/a-scope-lock-is-not-real-until-baseline-cash-out-and-threshold-are-frozen-in-the-same-burden-currency.md`
+- `runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-002-receptionist-search-attempt-003.md`
+
+## Exact Interaction Core Shared By All Three Candidates
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The desired Tao-like role couplings are the ordered five-channel
+  template inherited from the atlas packet:
+  `A -> B`,
+  `A -> C`,
+  `B,C -> C`,
+  `C,A <-> D`,
+  `D,D -> E`;
+  sources:
+  `atlas-anatomy-exploration-001-REPORT.md`,
+  `atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The exact forced extras that later steps must audit are:
+  mirror / conjugate companions,
+  same-scale companion triads,
+  long-leg feedback,
+  and cross-scale next-shell feedback;
+  source:
+  `atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md`.
+- `[VERIFIED]` Exact Leray / pressure projection is not a separate candidate.
+  It is the exact mechanism through which coefficient rigidity and spectator
+  leakage are enforced;
+  source:
+  `atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md`.
+
+## Candidate Interaction Sheets
+
+### 1. Template-Defect Near-Closure
+
+- Desired couplings:
+  the full role-projected five-channel vector field
+  `Q_clk, Q_seed, Q_amp, Q_rot^A, Q_rot^D, Q_next`
+  on one canonical packet family.
+- Automatically forced extra couplings:
+  all mirror companions of those channels,
+  same-scale companion targets hit by the same exact triads,
+  long-leg rotor feedback,
+  and next-shell feedback paired with `Q_next`.
+- Exact data Step 3 still needs:
+  the actual helical coefficients and signs on the chosen sign sheet,
+  phase dependence of repeated target-role sums,
+  and whether the role packet is stable under canonicalization choices.
+- One honest downstream gate:
+
+  ```text
+  G_tmpl(P_n; I) := (Delta_tmpl(P_n; I), Delta_spec(P_n; I))
+  ```
+
+  treated as one invariant template-defect observable on the fixed canonical
+  packet family and finite window.
+- Why this gate is right:
+  Step 3 can ask directly whether the same exact packet keeps the same template
+  defect after true symmetries are modded out and canonicalization choices are
+  frozen.
+
+### 2. Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget
+
+- Desired couplings:
+  the same five channels, but only as the denominator ledger `D_on`.
+- Automatically forced extra couplings:
+  every off-template channel in the mirror, companion, feedback, and cross
+  classes.
+- Exact data Step 3 still needs:
+  whether the spectator partition itself is stable under canonical conjugate
+  completion and helical-basis choices,
+  and whether any class budget is threshold-gerrymandered.
+- One honest downstream gate:
+
+  ```text
+  G_leak(P_n; I)
+    := (L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)
+  ```
+
+  treated as one hard admissibility sheet for later adversarial exact search.
+- Why this gate is right:
+  the final decider explicitly wanted hard admissibility filters and a
+  diagnostic vector rather than a soft score. This candidate is the most direct
+  place to use that rule.
+
+### 3. Delayed-Threshold Itinerary
+
+- Desired couplings:
+  the same five channels, but now only through the ordered sign / threshold
+  events they induce.
+- Automatically forced extra couplings:
+  any spectator channel that can reorder the events
+  `clock < trigger < rotor < next-stage transfer`
+  or can make the tiny trigger or slow clock cease to be gate-sized.
+- Exact data Step 3 still needs:
+  stability of the event times under canonicalization,
+  stability of the sign tests under the chosen helical sheet,
+  and whether the itinerary survives balanced anti-circuit and pro-circuit
+  packet families.
+- One honest downstream gate:
+
+  ```text
+  G_itin(P_n; I)
+    := (t_clk, t_trig, t_rot, t_next; sign sheet; spectator pass/fail)
+  ```
+
+  treated as one ordered-threshold admissibility sheet on the fixed packet
+  family and finite window.
+- Why this gate is right:
+  if a pro-near-circuit notion is going to survive honestly, it has to survive
+  at the level of ordered activation events, not only at the level of
+  coefficient rhetoric.
+
+## Step-3 Readiness Verdict
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Chain Step 3 is now well-posed.
+- Reasons:
+  - each promoted candidate now names one exact packet class;
+  - each candidate names one finite window and one threshold language;
+  - each candidate is attached to one exact interaction object rather than a
+    verbal mechanism memo;
+  - each candidate names exactly one downstream gate.
+- Survivors into Step 3:
+  `Template-Defect Near-Closure`,
+  `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`,
+  `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`.
+- Immediate failures:
+  none of the three promoted candidates fails at Step-2 definition level.
+  The unpromoted `projection-rigidity only` notion was filtered out before this
+  stage because it is not a distinct object.
+
+## Outcome
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Step 2 should close positively.
+- `[INFERRED]` The strongest theorem-facing candidates are:
+  `Template-Defect Near-Closure`
+  and
+  `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`.
+- `[INFERRED]` The strongest honest pro-near-circuit-friendly candidate is:
+  `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`,
+  but Step 3 must test whether it is robust after canonicalization rather than
+  just friendly in one chosen representation.

