+# Exploration 002 Summary
+
+## Goal
+
+Attach one exact Fourier/helical interaction template and one honest downstream
+gate to each promoted Step-2 candidate, then decide whether Chain Step 3 is
+well-posed.
+
+## What I Tried
+
+- Read the required Step-1, atlas, planning, judgment, and meta-screening
+  files first.
+- Checked the sibling Exploration 001 artifacts directly and found that they
+  were still only skeletons.
+- Recovered the intended promoted candidate family from the surviving local
+  record instead of pretending the empty Exploration 001 files settled it.
+- Wrote one shared packet/Fourier sheet, one interaction-template sheet per
+  recovered candidate, one downstream-gate ledger, and one Step-3 verdict.
+
+## Outcome
+
+- `succeeded`
+- `[INFERRED]` Step 3 is now well-posed for the recovered promoted family.
+
+## Key Takeaway
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The local record supports three honest Step-2 candidates:
+  `Role-Coupling Sheet`,
+  `Spectator-Leakage Screen`,
+  and
+  `Delayed-Threshold Behavior Screen`.
+  All three can be attached to the same exact role-labeled helical packet
+  object, and each now has one explicit Tao-role interaction template and one
+  honest downstream gate.
+
+## Leads Worth Pursuing
+
+- Compute one explicit wavevector/helicity family and the exact coefficient
+  ledger `C_{k,p,q}^{σ_k,σ_p,σ_q}` for the five Tao-role channels and all forced
+  companions.
+- Freeze one canonical coefficient-ratio sheet for the `Role-Coupling Sheet`
+  candidate before Step 3.
+- Freeze one invariant leakage observable and one exact partition of
+  `on-template` versus `spectator` channels for the `Spectator-Leakage Screen`
+  candidate.
+- Freeze one threshold sheet and one fixed activation window for the
+  `Delayed-Threshold Behavior Screen` candidate before Step 3 and Step 4.
+
+## Unexpected Findings
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The direct Exploration 001 report path was unusable because the
+  sibling `REPORT.md` and `REPORT-SUMMARY.md` were still skeletons.
+- `[INFERRED]` A pure graph-closure notion should not be promoted from this
+  record. The planning/judgment packet consistently points instead to a
+  coefficient-based notion, a leakage-based notion, and a behavior-based notion.
+
+## Computations Worth Doing Later
+
+- Write the exact projected amplitude equations for one canonically normalized
+  one-shell-bridge helical packet family, including all same-scale, conjugate,
+  and cross-scale forced modes.
+- Evaluate the leakage observable on that exact closed family over one fixed
+  finite window.
+- Test whether the delayed-threshold itinerary survives under limited phase,
+  helicity, and normalization variation after canonicalization is frozen.
